getting what I'm offering here.

24:18.911 --> 24:21.390
My government has yet to ratify the
Rome Statute,

24:21.391 --> 24:23.870
and therefore we still do not
recognise your court.

24:23.871 --> 24:26.630
But here is a perfect opportunity for us

24:26.631 --> 24:28.870
to take a big step towards that.

24:28.871 --> 24:30.950
I strongly advise you to grab it.

24:30.951 --> 24:33.310
Just because she's an old friend of
yours?

24:33.311 --> 24:36.190
Because she's the best prosecutor
there is.

24:36.191 --> 24:37.380
And you'll need her.

24:50.471 --> 24:52.200
You knew she was going to do that.

25:03.311 --> 25:04.351
We're on.

25:06.311 --> 25:07.870
You can't do it.

25:07.871 --> 25:09.630
- I've said yes.
- Say no!

25:09.631 --> 25:10.950
I understand your feelings...

25:10.951 --> 25:12.990
Which one? I have so many!

25:12.991 --> 25:14.590
I know it must feel very close...

25:14.591 --> 25:19.190
Close? General Nyamoya is a Rwandan
Tutsi, Mama.

25:19.191 --> 25:20.950
Who is accused of 13 counts of war...

25:20.951 --> 25:22.230
Who helped stop the genocide!

25:22.231 --> 25:23.575
And then he went into the Congo

25:23.600 --> 25:25.257
- and he did a lot of bad things...
- I'm a Rwandan Tutsi, Mama.

25:25.282 --> 25:26.670
No!

25:26.671 --> 25:29.590
You have a British passport and
you're my daughter.

25:29.591 --> 25:31.230
Yes, only because I survived.

25:31.231 --> 25:33.830
And without them, how would that
have happened?

25:33.831 --> 25:35.390
It's not so simple, darling.

25:35.391 --> 25:37.550
It is to me. I mean, to me, what
you're doing,

25:37.551 --> 25:39.550
it's like the Second World War is over,

25:39.551 --> 25:40.950
and we're Jewish, and suddenly,

25:40.951 --> 25:43.017
you've decided to prosecute
General Eisenhower

25:43.042 --> 25:44.510
because he tried to stop Hitler!

25:44.511 --> 25:46.470
Well, if Eisenhower had
committed war crimes,

25:46.471 --> 25:48.630
- he would have been prosecuted.
- Yes, but not by you!

25:48.631 --> 25:52.790
Not you, my mother, because for me,
it's like the SS is still out there,

25:52.791 --> 25:54.834
and all you're trying to do is prosecute

25:54.835 --> 25:57.151
one of the few men who tried to
stop them!

26:28.871 --> 26:32.780
Are you... Are you trying to drive a
wedge between us, Mama?

26:34.791 --> 26:36.511
Make me stand on my own two feet?

26:38.477 --> 26:39.877
Do you think you can't?

26:46.311 --> 26:48.390
Did you think I should?

26:48.391 --> 26:50.620
I think you're ready, yes.

26:51.191 --> 26:53.640
I think if you have me hovering
over you for the rest of your life,

26:53.665 --> 26:55.895
you'll never, ever fly.

26:57.471 --> 26:58.511
So...

26:59.511 --> 27:03.420
So all this is... Is what,
a way to cut me loose?

27:03.911 --> 27:05.020
No!

27:06.431 --> 27:09.270
You can't choose when something
happens, Kate.

27:09.271 --> 27:11.590
If it was 18 months ago, of course
I wouldn't have done it.

27:11.591 --> 27:15.340
But it's not, it's now, and now you
are better.

27:16.351 --> 27:18.190
And now I have to take this case.

27:18.191 --> 27:20.550
- But why?
- Because it's the right thing to do.

27:20.551 --> 27:21.591
Who...

27:22.671 --> 27:23.951
Who for?

27:25.271 --> 27:26.831
You?

27:26.856 --> 27:29.216
- Everyone.
- Not me.

27:29.241 --> 27:30.281
Everyone.

27:32.271 --> 27:33.311
Trust me.

27:35.791 --> 27:40.140
There are still men in the Congo

27:40.751 --> 27:43.300
responsible for the genocide, Mum.

27:44.151 --> 27:45.751
You want to do the right thing...

27:47.111 --> 27:48.511
...you should prosecute them.

28:32.610 --> 28:33.650
Ah, it's fine.

28:35.071 --> 28:36.590
- You sure?
- Yes, yes.

28:36.591 --> 28:39.470
It's just a mole. Not cancer.

28:39.471 --> 28:40.990
OK.

28:40.991 --> 28:43.030
It's quite large, though.

28:43.031 --> 28:45.550
I can remove it for you, peace of mind?

28:45.551 --> 28:48.030
No, no. It's fine.

28:48.031 --> 28:49.950
It's very simple. A few minutes, no
problem.

28:49.951 --> 28:51.631
No, no, no, no, no.

28:54.711 --> 28:56.551
I'll wait until I go home.

29:01.071 --> 29:02.950
You don't trust me?

29:02.951 --> 29:04.351
No, no, no, no. It's just...

29:05.431 --> 29:07.030
Well, you know.

29:07.031 --> 29:10.150
- Know what?
- It's fine, Doctor.

29:10.151 --> 29:12.030
Really. Thanks for looking.

29:12.031 --> 29:13.111
It's much appreciated.

29:30.831 --> 29:32.550
Do you want francs or dollars?

29:32.551 --> 29:35.019
You suspect I will flee the country?

29:35.020 --> 29:36.391
Francs.

29:41.271 --> 29:42.311
...the fuck?

29:44.431 --> 29:45.910
Who was that?

29:45.911 --> 29:47.831
- Who?
- That guy, just went through.

29:49.031 --> 29:50.071
I don't know.

29:52.871 --> 29:53.911
I do.

30:09.991 --> 30:11.780
You work for the hospital?

30:12.711 --> 30:13.991
Or do you work for him?

30:16.431 --> 30:19.551
Oh, it's OK. I already know.

30:29.671 --> 30:31.271
Major. Major!

30:32.311 --> 30:33.551
You've not paid.

30:34.831 --> 30:36.551
Do you know who that guy is?

30:37.380 --> 30:38.790
That guy is a war criminal with

30:38.791 --> 30:41.671
an international warrant on his head.

30:42.871 --> 30:44.110
No!

30:44.111 --> 30:45.910
Oh, yes.

30:45.911 --> 30:47.430
His name is Patrice Ganimana.

30:47.431 --> 30:50.990
He's like a Hutu general, took part
in the Rwanda genocide.

30:50.991 --> 30:54.670
He is responsible for the death of
about a million people.

30:54.671 --> 30:58.910
- No.
- Right here in your hospital.

30:58.911 --> 31:01.030
Sitting in a wheelchair.

31:01.031 --> 31:03.630
Pretty nurses and everything.

31:03.631 --> 31:04.671
Who?

31:07.863 --> 31:10.900
Patrice Ganimana.

31:13.886 --> 31:17.950
Yeah. He may not be the ace of spades,

31:17.951 --> 31:20.231
but he is certainly the 10 of clubs.

31:23.391 --> 31:24.620
Sometimes...

31:27.071 --> 31:29.671
...Europeans have difficulty telling
our faces apart.

31:30.791 --> 31:33.510
- No, no, no, no, no, no.
- You're mistaken.

31:33.511 --> 31:34.950
The fuck I am.

31:34.951 --> 31:36.430
Please, sir, you're in hospital.

31:36.431 --> 31:40.030
Yeah, and he should be in the Hague.

31:40.031 --> 31:41.220
Please.

31:41.897 --> 31:43.497
Just pay your bill.

31:52.791 --> 31:54.471
Aah...

31:57.324 --> 31:58.684
Keep the change.

32:09.317 --> 32:10.877
Oh, yeah.

32:15.631 --> 32:17.311
I know them.

32:18.351 --> 32:19.990
You haven't answered the question.

32:19.991 --> 32:22.310
And you haven't picked up that file.

32:22.311 --> 32:23.630
It's an immigration appeal.

32:23.631 --> 32:25.150
I'd like your opinion on it.

32:25.151 --> 32:28.151
Why did you give her the Nyamoya case?

32:29.511 --> 32:32.150
I'm not saying there is any pressure
on your room rental, Kate,

32:32.151 --> 32:34.710
but obviously I wouldn't be saying
it if there wasn't.

32:34.711 --> 32:37.670
They are prosecuting the wrong man
on the wrong side,

32:37.671 --> 32:39.590
and you've chosen the wrong person
to do it.

32:39.591 --> 32:41.060
Because he's a Tutsi?

32:42.129 --> 32:43.181
And so am I.

32:43.206 --> 32:45.910
And you'll be delighted when
the judge agrees with you.

32:45.911 --> 32:47.990
It isn't your world.

32:47.991 --> 32:49.591
- The Congo?
- The genocide.

32:51.671 --> 32:55.550
I prosecuted one of the first cases
for the ICTR in '98.

32:55.551 --> 32:57.390
Your mother was my junior.

32:57.391 --> 33:01.270
It's where we met. I'd go so far as
to say it's why you're here.

33:01.271 --> 33:05.034
And I don't want to go back to any
of it, ever.

33:06.951 --> 33:08.830
Do you think your mother loves you, Kate?

33:08.831 --> 33:10.870
You think she'd ever do anything to
harm you?

33:10.871 --> 33:14.710
- It's a silly question.
- It is, so why do you keep asking it?

33:14.711 --> 33:16.567
Your mother is one of the most steadfast

33:16.592 --> 33:18.190
and loyal people I have ever met,

33:18.191 --> 33:21.350
and most of that has been directed
at you.

33:21.351 --> 33:23.150
She's also one of the smartest.

33:23.151 --> 33:26.024
So if she's chosen to prosecute
Simon Nyamoya,

33:26.025 --> 33:29.031
I'd trust her to do it.
Let her do her job, Kate.

33:30.031 --> 33:31.460
And you...

33:32.031 --> 33:34.351
...do yours. I'd like that back in
the morning.

33:47.311 --> 33:48.791
- Oh, Miss Ashby.
- Hi, Frank.

33:50.431 --> 33:51.471
Sweetheart?

33:53.351 --> 33:56.340
Sweetheart, would you close the door?

33:57.551 --> 33:59.711
- Yes.
- Thank you.

34:10.231 --> 34:11.791
Mine's a flat white.

34:17.710 --> 34:19.710
Are you taking on a new case?

34:19.710 --> 34:21.110
Just an opinion.

34:22.511 --> 34:23.551
Well, that's a start.

34:25.751 --> 34:27.500
I didn't think this was allowed.

34:28.670 --> 34:30.030
Um-hmm?

34:30.031 --> 34:33.230
Thought we weren't allowed to be in
the same room together.

34:33.231 --> 34:36.781
- Um-hmm. Of course we are.
- Alone.

34:42.929 --> 34:44.260
I'm leaving, Kate.

34:47.958 --> 34:48.981
What?

34:49.005 --> 34:51.614
Your mother's asked me to be her
permanent rep at the Nyamoya case.

34:55.110 --> 34:56.391
You're going to the Hague?

34:58.471 --> 35:00.180
- Yep.
- Wow.

35:01.191 --> 35:02.910
I mean, she only got it yesterday.

35:02.911 --> 35:03.951
Yeah, but...

35:04.991 --> 35:06.140
We saw it coming.

35:07.231 --> 35:09.671
- How?
- All I know is

35:10.780 --> 35:14.950
everyone was pushing Nyamoya to
hand himself in.

35:14.951 --> 35:17.310
The DRC, Rwanda,

35:17.311 --> 35:19.230
us, the Americans.

35:19.231 --> 35:21.271
- Everyone.
- Why?

35:22.871 --> 35:23.898
He was a warlord.

35:23.923 --> 35:25.790
There are others still
out there, far worse.

35:25.791 --> 35:26.990
Oh.

35:26.991 --> 35:28.700
Same thing's happening to them.

35:29.671 --> 35:33.340
- I haven't seen it.
- Yes, we have.

35:35.831 --> 35:37.550
There's a genocide...

35:37.551 --> 35:38.591
Genocide.

35:40.191 --> 35:42.980
Look, the region just wants to move
on, Kate.

35:45.511 --> 35:46.551
A fresh start.

35:52.151 --> 35:53.471
So should you.

36:16.984 --> 36:18.984
FIB have been informed.

36:19.191 --> 36:21.510
And when do you think they'll show up?

36:21.511 --> 36:24.780
Well, next week, next month, next year?

36:25.671 --> 36:28.190
And, how long does it take to get an
X-ray?

36:28.191 --> 36:29.950
Because I think that's what he was
having.

36:29.951 --> 36:32.110
What are you trying to do here, Major?

36:32.111 --> 36:35.270
Not to repeat past mistakes, sir.

36:35.271 --> 36:39.830
- Like?
- Well, I come from Quebec,

36:39.831 --> 36:43.301
and the last time a Canadian was in
charge of this sort of thing was

36:43.302 --> 36:46.380
over in Rwanda during the genocide.

36:47.711 --> 36:49.151
It didn't end so well.

36:50.151 --> 36:52.711
I'm hoping the same thing won't
happen to me.

36:53.751 --> 36:59.471
Or, and with the greatest respect,
sir, to you.

37:00.511 --> 37:02.030
Me?

37:02.031 --> 37:03.420
You're French.

37:04.151 --> 37:06.430
Some people think it was you guys
back then

37:06.431 --> 37:08.031
that helped people like this

37:08.917 --> 37:11.631
Ganimana here to escape in the first
place.

37:13.911 --> 37:15.150
Not me, Major.

37:15.151 --> 37:17.511
In '94 I was reading Lucky Luke.

37:19.151 --> 37:24.910
Well, then you better hope that some
of that has rubbed off.

37:24.911 --> 37:27.860
You carry on like this, you're going
to need it.

37:30.644 --> 37:32.604
SHOUTED COMMAND

37:32.910 --> 37:34.230
IN FRENCH: Continuez.

37:39.831 --> 37:40.871
Man.

37:50.751 --> 37:52.230
Oh, Evie.

37:52.231 --> 37:53.911
Save it for the judge.

37:59.671 --> 38:04.151
You may want to choose a corner, there.

38:10.151 --> 38:13.551
There's not a day passed I hadn't
thought of telling her.

38:15.591 --> 38:16.631
And when she...

38:18.071 --> 38:21.790
...when she tried to do what she did,
I knew why I hadn't.

38:21.791 --> 38:23.471
It's what we all agreed.

38:25.071 --> 38:26.190
But what if I was wrong?

38:26.191 --> 38:28.070
What if it's the other way round?

38:28.071 --> 38:31.710
What if she only did what she did
precisely because I hadn't told her?

38:31.711 --> 38:33.270
You can't think like that.

38:33.271 --> 38:35.590
No, because it damns me both ways.

38:35.591 --> 38:37.790
You rescued a child.

38:37.791 --> 38:38.991
And you gave her a life.

38:40.431 --> 38:41.871
But not her past.

38:42.500 --> 38:44.471
And you're about to do that, too.

38:46.111 --> 38:47.950
Well, what if I was right in the
first place?

38:47.951 --> 38:49.671
And what if she's still not ready?

38:56.511 --> 38:58.150
That it?

38:58.151 --> 38:59.471
Yes.

39:03.911 --> 39:06.260
Maybe you should have let me
take the case.

39:07.085 --> 39:08.390
She's my daughter!

39:08.391 --> 39:10.910
But it's not just about her now, is it?

39:10.911 --> 39:14.030
It's about that, and this.

39:14.031 --> 39:16.470
And seeing this done at last.

39:16.471 --> 39:18.230
I know what it's about, Michael.

39:18.231 --> 39:20.990
Well, then you've answered during
question, haven't you?

39:20.991 --> 39:23.630
This is our chance. It might not
come again.

39:23.631 --> 39:25.311
We got to take it while we can.

39:27.537 --> 39:29.657
You're right, of course you are.

39:29.682 --> 39:31.442
Been a long time coming.

39:34.124 --> 39:35.404
Over 20 years.

39:36.911 --> 39:40.580
And sometimes I feel whatever it is
we've been holding out for,

39:41.237 --> 39:43.437
or clinging onto, I don't know...

39:46.631 --> 39:48.940
It's dragged me out so far...

39:51.311 --> 39:53.151
...I'm not sure I can never get back.

39:55.660 --> 39:56.980
But, I mean, you will.

39:58.591 --> 40:01.260
You'll be fine, and so will Kate.

40:19.671 --> 40:21.220
I wish we'd fallen in love.

40:22.231 --> 40:23.271
Well, we didn't.

40:24.991 --> 40:26.711
Why we're still friends.

40:35.591 --> 40:38.110
She has connections with Rwanda?

40:38.111 --> 40:40.830
Oh, yes. She adopted a Rwandan child,

40:40.831 --> 40:45.550
and she helped prosecute one of the
first cases after the genocide.

40:45.551 --> 40:48.870
Against the men who carried out
the genocide?

40:48.871 --> 40:52.231
Yep. Which I helped bring to an end.

40:53.391 --> 40:56.350
So, she and I...

40:56.351 --> 40:57.900
...we are on the same side.

41:00.471 --> 41:02.871
- We better hope so.
- There is no hope about it.

41:04.631 --> 41:08.500
We are on the same side.

41:13.311 --> 41:14.870
It's not about sides.

41:14.871 --> 41:16.060
Isn't it?

41:16.551 --> 41:19.670
Back then, you and Nyamoya were
chasing the same thing.

41:19.671 --> 41:23.110
Evil Hutus. You as a lawyer, him as
a soldier.

41:23.111 --> 41:27.150
And because of that, you're asking
me to do what, exactly?

41:27.151 --> 41:29.430
To remove him from the field, no doubt.

41:29.431 --> 41:31.190
But also, perhaps,

41:31.191 --> 41:34.790
to allow him to return to an
entirely peaceful retirement

41:34.791 --> 41:38.380
in the not too distant future.
He was a hero, after all.

41:39.751 --> 41:40.791
A hero?

41:42.871 --> 41:45.900
Just because you asked me to forget,
doesn't mean I did.

41:48.471 --> 41:51.590
The indictment accuses him of the
enlistment of child soldiers for the

41:51.591 --> 41:54.950
purposes of war in the DRC from 2004...

41:54.951 --> 41:57.471
- It's not the date I'm interested in.
- ..to 2006.

41:59.151 --> 42:01.111
- Then, which?
- I just told you.

42:02.271 --> 42:04.220
The one you asked me to forget.

42:04.990 --> 42:06.110
Back then.

42:27.511 --> 42:28.950
I thought I was visiting a friend?

42:28.951 --> 42:30.430
Friends don't ask people to lie.

42:30.431 --> 42:32.150
And friends don't try to undermine you.

42:32.151 --> 42:34.070
By telling them the truth?

42:34.071 --> 42:36.590
David, isn't that exactly what
friends are for?

42:36.591 --> 42:39.990
Oh, Eve, we are used to seeing
zealots in dog collars,

42:39.991 --> 42:42.270
but not in horsehair wigs.

42:42.271 --> 42:43.831
Neither will save my country.

42:46.631 --> 42:48.740
It's a little more complex than that.

42:50.511 --> 42:51.551
Isn't it?

42:53.991 --> 42:56.390
We have a duty to memory.

42:56.391 --> 42:57.431
Whose?

42:58.551 --> 42:59.780
Hers?

43:00.551 --> 43:02.066
Yours?

43:02.067 --> 43:03.431
Everyone's.

43:07.071 --> 43:08.630
Some things are best left forgotten.

43:08.631 --> 43:09.671
Not this.

43:11.751 --> 43:15.140
Tell them now, David, now that the
going's good.

43:28.591 --> 43:29.991
Thank you for the drink.

43:51.431 --> 43:54.940
And for what you did for us,
all of those years ago.

44:15.577 --> 44:16.777
Aah.

44:16.991 --> 44:21.070
- Transfer. I want to stay...
- Hey, Harper.

44:21.071 --> 44:24.310
- Mikey.
- How's my girl today?

44:24.311 --> 44:26.190
Oh, grand.

44:26.191 --> 44:28.910
- Just grand.
- What you reading her?

44:28.911 --> 44:30.270
Just an old Graham Greene.

44:30.271 --> 44:31.511
Oh, she'll love that.

44:34.631 --> 44:35.671
So...

44:37.111 --> 44:38.260
I'm on my way.

44:39.911 --> 44:42.671
Great, thanks, Harvey.

44:45.871 --> 44:47.550
Next time.

44:47.551 --> 44:49.190
Great.

44:49.191 --> 44:51.460
- Give my love to Jenny.
- Bye, Hannah.

44:58.671 --> 45:01.180
He's better for your mother,
wouldn't you say?

45:02.380 --> 45:03.831
Much, much better.

45:05.951 --> 45:07.220
Oh.

45:07.911 --> 45:09.700
You've got some colour in your cheeks.

45:11.431 --> 45:12.471
That's nice.

45:17.057 --> 45:18.297
Oh.

45:19.431 --> 45:22.140
The Nyamoya case is about to begin.

45:23.717 --> 45:26.820
I don't think it will give us all
the answers, but it's a start.

45:29.631 --> 45:30.990
It's a start, darling.

45:30.991 --> 45:35.111
And Daddy'll find the end, I promise.

45:39.111 --> 45:40.991
So, where we at?

45:55.551 --> 45:57.710
Frank? My mother just called.

45:57.711 --> 46:00.711
She needs me to pick something up
from her office on my way home.

46:46.951 --> 46:48.791
Is she still in there?

46:55.551 --> 46:59.031
Give that to me. Give it to me now!

47:05.631 --> 47:08.070
- How much did you see?
- I...

47:08.071 --> 47:09.630
It's illegal, what you're doing.

47:09.631 --> 47:10.671
It's illegal.

47:12.311 --> 47:14.430
Is... Is this a taxi rank job?

47:14.431 --> 47:15.710
You didn't have a choice?

47:15.711 --> 47:17.590
Of course I did.

47:17.591 --> 47:19.910
And I... I just...

47:19.911 --> 47:22.100
I don't understand. Why?

47:28.591 --> 47:30.431
Take a long, hard look.

47:32.071 --> 47:33.351
Look at it.

47:37.503 --> 47:38.940
And you remember it.

47:40.071 --> 47:43.171
Remember it. And then one day,

47:43.172 --> 47:46.231
hopefully, one day soon
you'll understand.

47:47.511 --> 47:49.100
Take a look at this.

47:49.671 --> 47:51.671
Take a good, hard look.

47:53.071 --> 47:54.871
This is what they did to me.

47:56.831 --> 47:58.471
I don't remember my family.

47:59.471 --> 48:01.020
Or my country.

48:01.631 --> 48:02.671
Nothing.

48:03.871 --> 48:06.710
I don't know my own name!

48:06.711 --> 48:11.082
The only thing I know is that it
happened to nearly a million people,

48:11.083 --> 48:13.935
and I will never forget it, and
neither should anyone else.

48:13.936 --> 48:14.955
And no-one will.

48:14.980 --> 48:17.575
Except you're going to
give them the excuse!

48:19.311 --> 48:21.631
I don't know what's in there.

48:23.351 --> 48:24.671
But it won't match this.

48:26.111 --> 48:30.670
But you push that, and everyone can
go back to what they really think.

48:30.671 --> 48:34.230
That down there, genocide, war crimes,

48:34.231 --> 48:36.231
that's just what they all do
to each other!

48:37.671 --> 48:40.231
That we're all just cats in a bag!

48:42.271 --> 48:44.551
That we're all just monkeys!

48:46.231 --> 48:48.110
I don't give a shit what they think
up here.

48:48.111 --> 48:50.070
I'm only talking to the people that
matter,

48:50.071 --> 48:52.750
and if they don't want to see their
country turn into another...

48:52.751 --> 48:55.150
- The arrogance!
- ..Into another fucking Yugoslavia,

48:55.151 --> 48:57.089
they'll need to listen.

48:57.090 --> 48:58.311
And so will you.

49:01.071 --> 49:03.631
And you're the only one to tell us.

49:04.911 --> 49:05.951
Yes, I am.

49:08.071 --> 49:09.351
I really, really am.

49:11.751 --> 49:14.260
Spoken like a true Mzungu.

49:23.551 --> 49:25.631
Don't. I'm leaving tomorrow.

49:30.271 --> 49:34.791
And I will never understand why.

49:35.991 --> 49:38.631
Don't expect me at... home.

49:48.111 --> 50:00.791
♪ A charge to keep I have

50:02.031 --> 50:13.351
♪ A God to glorify

50:16.031 --> 50:28.071
♪ A never-dying soul to save

50:29.975 --> 50:41.511
♪ And fit it for the sky. ♪

51:07.071 --> 51:09.110
It's Corporal Benoit, right?

51:09.111 --> 51:10.151
Sir!

51:13.191 --> 51:15.511
You want to make a difference, Corporal?

51:17.951 --> 51:19.191
Then don't end up like me.

51:24.031 --> 51:25.790
CAR ENGINE RUNNING

51:25.791 --> 51:27.671
BANG

51:38.711 --> 51:39.780
Mum!

51:40.810 --> 51:42.140
Mum!

51:43.597 --> 51:44.940
Mama!

51:45.397 --> 51:47.140
Mum!

51:48.871 --> 51:50.231
Mum!

52:11.631 --> 52:13.298
- Mama...
- VOICE MAIL: Please leave a message

52:13.323 --> 52:14.780
after the tone.

52:15.671 --> 52:18.430
It's me. I'm sorry.

52:18.431 --> 52:20.670
I'm sorry, Mum. What I said was
unforgivable.

52:20.671 --> 52:23.031
I'm sorry. I love you.

52:25.391 --> 52:26.791
Call me.

52:47.711 --> 52:49.950
I know who owns these vehicles.

52:49.951 --> 52:53.270
Your boss is one of the most wanted
men in Africa.

52:53.271 --> 52:55.180
Now, where is he?

52:56.098 --> 52:57.263
Where is he?

52:57.264 --> 52:58.860
Tennis! Tennis!

52:59.471 --> 53:00.790
On Doctor's orders.

53:00.791 --> 53:02.271
Secure the area!

53:08.031 --> 53:09.950
What the fuck do you think you are doing?

53:09.951 --> 53:11.860
Oh, what does it look like I'm doing?

53:12.740 --> 53:13.916
Stand them down.

53:13.941 --> 53:17.135
This is an indictment
against Patrice Ganimana.

53:18.591 --> 53:20.231
It is not a warrant.

53:21.511 --> 53:22.950
It'll have to do.

53:22.951 --> 53:25.111
Apparently, he's playing tennis.

53:28.471 --> 53:29.511
Stand...

53:30.991 --> 53:32.031
...them...

53:33.231 --> 53:34.551
...down.

53:42.310 --> 53:44.310
We're blue hats, Colonel.

53:45.517 --> 53:47.597
You can't shoot until you're shot at.

53:50.831 --> 53:53.271
GUNSHOTS

53:54.871 --> 53:57.820
Who fired? Who fired?

54:16.551 --> 54:19.711
Weapon down! Weapon down!

54:21.671 --> 54:25.431
On your knees. On your knees.

54:26.791 --> 54:30.031
Who fired first? Who fired first?!

54:34.951 --> 54:38.430
Please...

54:38.431 --> 54:40.820
Fuck, fuck, fuck!

54:42.471 --> 54:45.470
Shit. Shit. Christ.

54:45.471 --> 54:48.460
Benoit. Benoit!

54:49.944 --> 54:51.424
Medic!

54:54.971 --> 54:56.931
Medic!

54:57.111 --> 54:59.230
Oh, shit.

54:59.231 --> 55:01.151
Fuck.

55:04.631 --> 55:05.991
Please...

55:15.831 --> 55:18.700
Oh, fuck. You're not Ganimana.

55:20.111 --> 55:23.791
Oh, fuck. You're not Patrice Ganimana.

55:28.031 --> 55:31.111
But I saw him. I know it.

55:35.951 --> 55:37.791
Christ!

55:49.471 --> 55:52.510
Look, I can only say what I always have,

55:52.511 --> 55:56.630
that although this place may be many
thousands of miles from the events

55:56.631 --> 56:01.910
upon which it must adjudicate,
I believe that what we do here,

56:01.911 --> 56:03.350
particularly now,

56:03.351 --> 56:07.300
when nations are turning their backs
on international responsibility,

56:07.671 --> 56:10.300
what happens here becomes all the
more important

56:10.820 --> 56:13.900
for countries that have
no recourse to justice,

56:14.311 --> 56:17.231
for people who believe that day will
never come.

56:18.551 --> 56:20.151
We're trying to make a difference.

56:22.231 --> 56:23.511
Thank you.

57:25.231 --> 57:26.871
No matter what.

57:52.404 --> 57:53.884
GUNSHOT

